                        	<a name="story5"><span style="font-family:headerfont;">04.24.12</span></a><br />
<span style="color:#ffcc00; text-transform:uppercase;">First Look at DGA</span><br />First Look, the broad ranging USC School of Cinematic Arts annual student showcase, returns to the Directors Guild of America on April 24-26. Featuring original works from students in the Film and Television Production Division and the Peter Stark Producing Program, The John C. Hench Division of Animation & Digital Arts and the Interactive Media Division, First Look is an exhibition, held over the course of three evenings, that gives students the opportunity to share their work with an audience of friends, family and entertainment industry members.  
<br /><br />
The following week, students from Writing for Screen and Television Division will participate in <em><b>First Pitch</b></em>, the annual event where students 'pitch' their screenplay ideas to dozens of agents, managers, and film and television executives.
<br /><br />
"First Look is a forum for students to reveal their finest work, across all platforms, and it's proven year in and year out to provide essential exposure of student work to industry professionals," said Dean Elizabeth M. Daley. "It's a wonderful stepping stone which helps students transcend the academic world and step into the entertainment industry."
<br /><br />
The Festival Highlights: 

<ul><li><em><b>First Film</b></em> is presented by the Office of Student Industry Relations on April 24 and showcases short films from the SCA Film & Television Production Division and Peter Stark Producing Program. The featured films are selected at the end of a two-day screening series at USC preceding the DGA event. Sponsored by FotoKem, filmmaker awards will be presented that evening.</li>

<li><em><b>Adobe First Frame</b></em> will include animation and installation art from students in the John C. Hench Division of Animation and Digital Arts (Hench-DADA) on April 25.</li>

<li><em><b>First Move</b></em> will showcase interactive projects and games from students in the Interactive Media Division on April 26. Additionally, the First Move Interactive Gallery will be open all three evenings in the DGA atrium, allowing guests the opportunity to interact directly with many student projects.</li>

<li><em><b>First Pitch</b></em> will provide a forum for graduating M.F.A. and B.F.A. screenwriting students to solicit or "pitch" their film and television scripts to participating members of the industry's top production companies, management firms and agencies on April 30 at the Four Seasons Hotel in Beverly Hills. This event is closed to the public.</li></ul>

All evening screenings and presentations at the Directors Guild of America begin at 7:30 pm. The DGA is located at 7920 Sunset Blvd., Los Angeles, CA 90046. 
<br /><br />
For more information please visit <a href="http://cinema.usc.edu/FirstLook" target="_blank">cinema.usc.edu/FirstLook</a>. 
